body:
hi, all,
I look more into this issue, and I feel I need to accept Dave's proposal as the best option to fix this issue. That is, fix current isHiddenColumn() 'len - 1' issue and proceed with it.  And I added regression test for this change.
The proposal made by Selva and Hans to use NAColumn method is good. However, it is very difficult to  implement. As far as I understand up to now, it needs many changes to current code.
First, inside this RefConstraint::getPredicateText() method, each NAColumn object in the 'keyColumns' will NEVER return differently for any NAColumn::isXXColumn(), except the isUserColumn(), all other methods return false. The reason is: these objects are not properly initialized. 
The root where these objects are created is at:
 AbstractRIConstraint::setKeyColumns()
This line of code is how these NAColumns are created:
  column = new (heap) NAColumn(colDesc->colname, colDesc->position, NULL, heap);
So any attributes are NOT set at this point. And look further, where all column info is get from inside this setKeyColumns() method? It is from a class named constrnts_desc_struct.

struct constrnts_desc_struct {
  char *constrntname;
  char *tablename;
  ConstraintType type;
  Int32  colcount;
  Int32  isEnforced;
  char *indexname;
  desc_struct *check_constrnts_desc;
  desc_struct *constr_key_cols_desc;
  desc_struct *referenced_constrnts_desc;
  desc_struct *referencing_constrnts_desc;
#ifdef NA_LITTLE_ENDIAN
  void encode() {}
#endif
};

As one can see, there is NO information about column details like SALT, DIVISION, SYSKEY , etc...
So if we do need to create a NAColumn object which can correctly behave on isSaltColumn(), we have to change this constrnts_desc_struct.

However, look deeper into the code, all information that filled in the constrnts_desc_struct are come from a query from METADATA table TRAFODION._MD_.TABLE_CONSTRAINTS'. So I think we have to save the corresponding attributes like SALT,DIVISION,SYSKEY in this metadata table. This is complex and break backward compatibility. 

Another way, is when generate the column list in the TRAFODION._MD_.TABLE_CONSTRAINTS', filter out SALT,DIVISION,SYSKEY columns. However, this will have side effect which I cannot study out in a short time. If going into this way, the effort to solve this simple defect will be so insane. 

So , I admit that creating a new isHiddenColumn() function have shortcomings:
1. Itself may be incorrect, not well tested in all scenarios.
2. it must change when SALT, DIVISION, SYSKEY name conversion changed.

For 1, we have to do more tests.
For 2, I add some comments in this function to indicate this issue. And I saw there is a JIRA TRAFODION-1852 that will standardize these names as KeyWords, so for compatibility, I assume, these names will not change unless there is a strong reason.

Given, all above, I decided to go with my original code and abandon the effort to try to use NAColumn.isSaltColumn(), etc.

Hope all can agree and get this merged. This is a real blocking issue for real customers. A not perfect fix , but better than no fix.

i will commit a new version very soon,
- fixing Dave's comments about 'len -1'
- add test cases
- add some comments for isHiddenColumn()

